Techint Wants to Buy Argentina’s Ternium Stake, La Nacion Says

-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 
2011-05-04T11:23:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/techint-wants-to-buy-argentina-s-ternium-stake-la-nacion-says.html
The Techint Group is willing to buy
the Argentine government’s 26 percent stake in  Siderar SAIC (ERAR) , the
local unit of  Ternium SA (TX) , La Nacion  said , citing Ternium
Chairman Paolo Rocca.  “We are willing to buy” the Argentine pensions agency’s
stake, Rocca, whose family controls Techint, was cited by the
Buenos Aires-based newspaper as saying.  Techint has filed a legal complaint against a government
decree that allows the government to exercise full voting rights
in companies in which it holds shares, the newspaper said.  Techint is the controlling shareholder of Ternium.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in Buenos Aires at 
 rorihuela@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  